00:11:14,853 --> 00:11:16,235
where the Taj Mahal is built.

253
00:11:16,235 --> 00:11:22,325
That place has been referred to in multiple sources as 'Haveli', 'Khana', and 'Manzil'.

254
00:11:22,325 --> 00:11:25,485
Different sources use different words.

255
00:11:25,485 --> 00:11:27,595
But these words were used to mean home.

256
00:11:27,595 --> 00:11:30,923
Small or big, Raja Jai Singh's home was there.

257
00:11:30,923 --> 00:11:34,918
Raja Jai Singh actually wanted to donate his land for free,

258
00:11:34,918 --> 00:11:36,674
to build the tomb for the Emperess.

259
00:11:36,674 --> 00:11:38,915
Historian Ira Mukhtoy tells us,

260
00:11:38,915 --> 00:11:41,607
that this is because the royals of Jaipur,

261
00:11:41,607 --> 00:11:43,584
had close relations to the Mughals

262
00:11:43,584 --> 00:11:47,322
after Akbar's marriage to Amer's Harka Bai.

263
00:11:47,322 --> 00:11:49,363
Bollywood films will have us believe that

264
00:11:49,363 --> 00:11:51,557
Akbar's wife's name was Jodha Bai.

265
00:11:51,557 --> 00:11:53,482
As shown in the picture Jodha Akbar,

266
00:11:53,482 --> 00:11:57,158
A good film, but in this instance, historically incorrect.

267
00:11:57,158 --> 00:12:00,306
Jodha Bai literally means a Lady from Jodhpur.

268
00:12:00,306 --> 00:12:02,290
But it was Jahangir,

269
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:06,328
who had married the daughter of Jodhpur's ruler, Raja Uday Singh.

270
00:12:06,328 --> 00:12:08,577
His daughter was Jagat Gosain.

271
00:12:08,577 --> 00:12:10,975
She was Shah Jahan's mother.

272
00:12:10,975 --> 00:12:14,529
Back then, a British East India Company officer,

273
00:12:14,529 --> 00:12:16,289
Lt Col James Todd,

274
00:12:16,289 --> 00:12:20,506
wrote a book Annals and Antiquities of Rajasthan.

275
00:12:20,506 --> 00:12:23,075
In that book, he had mistakenly mentioned

276
00:12:23,075 --> 00:12:25,163
Jodha Bai instead of Harka Bai.

277
00:12:25,163 --> 00:12:27,122
That's why people have this confusion

278
00:12:27,122 --> 00:12:29,346
that Jodha Bai was Akbar's wife.

279
00:12:29,346 --> 00:12:31,487
Akbar's wife was Harka Bai,

280
00:12:31,487 --> 00:12:34,011
she was Raja Maan Singh's aunt.

281
00:12:34,011 --> 00:12:36,645
And Raja Maan Singh was the trusted general of Akbar.

282
00:12:36,645 --> 00:12:38,562
Shah Jahan was Akbar's grandson,

283
00:12:38,562 --> 00:12:41,082
and Raja Jai Singh was Raja Maan Singh's grandson.

284
00:12:41,082 --> 00:12:45,042
You can now understand why the two had such close relations.

285
00:12:45,042 --> 00:12:46,726
Raja Jai Singh and Shah Jahan.

286
00:12:46,726 --> 00:12:50,230
This is why Raja Jai Singh offered his land for free

287
00:12:50,230 --> 00:12:52,205
he wanted to donate it to Shah Jahan,

288
00:12:52,205 --> 00:12:55,087
so that Shah Jahan could build a tomb for Mumtaz.

289
00:12:55,087 --> 00:12:59,242
