00:14:25,910 --> 00:14:27,655
That are now being repeated everywhere.

321
00:14:27,655 --> 00:14:30,185
The answer to this, friends, is one person,

322
00:14:30,185 --> 00:14:32,161
Purushottam Nagesh Oak,

323
00:14:32,161 --> 00:14:34,475
also known as P.N. Oak.

324
00:14:34,475 --> 00:14:38,237
He was the person who came up with the claim of Tejo Mahalaya.

325
00:14:38,237 --> 00:14:40,769
Interestingly, he was not a historian.

326
00:14:40,769 --> 00:14:42,348
He was a history enthusiast,

327
00:14:42,348 --> 00:14:44,380
and enjoyed writing history as well.

328
00:14:44,380 --> 00:14:45,653
But he wasn't a historian

329
00:14:45,653 --> 00:14:47,794
because he made up his version of history.

330
00:14:47,794 --> 00:14:49,536
He rewrote history.

331
00:14:49,536 --> 00:14:52,105
Friends, the methodology of historians

332
00:14:52,105 --> 00:14:54,278
is extensive and tiring.

333
00:14:54,723 --> 00:14:57,740
A historian has to look through old newspapers and magazines,

334
00:14:57,740 --> 00:15:00,724
diary entries, letters,

335
00:15:00,724 --> 00:15:04,220
painting, historical accounts of court historians,

336
00:15:04,220 --> 00:15:06,340
accounts of contemporary historians,

337
00:15:06,340 --> 00:15:09,117
accounts of travellers, carbon dating,

338
00:15:09,117 --> 00:15:12,672
and then they have to analyse them to understand

339
00:15:12,672 --> 00:15:14,635
what would have happened back then.

340
00:15:14,635 --> 00:15:17,716
After they've understood it, they have to write it down,

341
00:15:17,716 --> 00:15:21,629
and create an account by citing the various sources they've relied on.

342
00:15:21,629 --> 00:15:24,669
Then their writing is peer-reviewed,

343
00:15:24,669 --> 00:15:26,461
by other historians,

344
00:15:26,461 --> 00:15:28,723
to check how accurate

345
00:15:28,723 --> 00:15:30,989
the account written by the historian.

346
00:15:30,989 --> 00:15:33,679
But P.N. Oak's methodology was vastly different from it.

347
00:15:33,679 --> 00:15:35,336
The methodology he used worked somewhat like this.

348
00:15:35,336 --> 00:15:39,726
Since the word Vatican sounds similar to the Sanskrit word 'Vatika',

349
00:15:39,726 --> 00:15:43,506
he'd write that it was probable that Vatican had once been a Hindu temple.

350
00:15:43,506 --> 00:15:46,328
He didn't stop at 'probable', he wrote it as if that was the truth.

351
00:15:46,328 --> 00:15:48,766
Westminster Abbey was also a Hindu temple,

352
00:15:48,766 --> 00:15:50,519
And I'm not joking, guys.

353
00:15:50,519 --> 00:15:54,288
These were the things written by P.N. Oak in his pamphlets.

354
00:15:54,288 --> 00:15:56,721
If you think these sound weird,

355
00:15:56,721 --> 00:15:58,809
he has written things way weirder than these.

356
00:15:58,809 --> 00:16:01,294
He had written a pamphlet on Christianity.

357
00:16:01,294 --> 00:16:04,600
He said that Christianity is actually Chrisn-Nity. [ideology of Hindu deity Krishna]

358
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:07,020
According to him, Jesus Christ had visited India,

359
00:16:07,020 --> 00:16:09,512
between the ages of 13 and 30 years old,

360
00:16:09,512 --> 00:16:11,987
and he had learned Krishna's ideologies here.

361
00:16:11,987 --> 00:16:13,920
And so the entirety of Christianity

362
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:15,737
is therefore inspired by Hinduism.

363
00:16:15,737 --> 00:16:17,538
Not only this, but he also claimed that

364
00:16:17,538 --> 00:16:21,289
Islam and Judaism too have come from Hinduism.

365
00:16:21,289 --> 00:16:22,710
How?

366
00:16:22,710 --> 00:16:25,987
Because Abraham sounds like Brahma.

367
00:16:25,987 --> 00:16:27,722
Abraham's wife Sarah,

368
00:16:27,722 --> 00:16:28,949
was probably Saraswati,

369
00:16:28,949 --> 00:16:31,474
Moses would be Mahesh aka Shiv.

370
00:16:31,474 --> 00:16:35,592
In fact, according to him, the entire world was ruled by an ancient Hindu empire.

371
00:16:35,592 --> 00:16:37,315
Coming back to the topic of the Taj Mahal,

372
00:16:37,315 --> 00:16:42,092
it was P.N. Oak who created this conspiracy theory about the Taj Mahal.

373
00:16:42,092 --> 00:16:45,104
In his opinion, the Mughals didn't build any monuments.

374
00:16:45,104 --> 00:16:49,505
Initially, P.N. Oak said that the Taj Mahal was a wonder of ancient Hinduism,

375
00:16:49,505 --> 00:16:50,991
built in ancient times.

376
00:16:50,991 --> 00:16:55,649
The historians refuted this by saying that buildings from before the 4th century

377
00:16:55,649 --> 00:16:58,758
have only survived is they were made by cutting out rocks.

378
00:16:58,758 --> 00:17:00,802
No other buildings have survived.

379
00:17:00,802 --> 00:17:02,292
So this couldn't be possible.

380
00:17:02,292 --> 00:17:04,577
The Taj Mahal was actually built in the 1600s.

381
00:17:04,577 --> 00:17:07,138
After this, Oak revised his claim.

382
00:17:07,138 --> 00:17:11,314
Then he said that it was built in the year 1155,

383
00:17:11,314 --> 00:17:13,144
by Raja Paramardi Dev.

384
00:17:13,144 --> 00:17:15,444
By the Chief Minister of the Raja Dev.

385
00:17:15,444 --> 00:17:19,079
When history is so close to home, it doesn't take long to be revised.

386
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:23,010
In 1989, he wrote another pamphlet titled

387
00:17:23,010 --> 00:17:24,987
Taj Mahal: The True Story.

388
00:17:24,987 --> 00:17:26,759
On the basis of his own pamphlet,

389
00:17:26,759 --> 00:17:29,840
he filed a PIL in the court in 2000 saying that

390
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:32,011
we need to know the truth behind it.

391
00:17:32,011 --> 00:17:34,724
Interestingly, in court, he had also cited that

392
00:17:34,724 --> 00:17:37,231
Shah Jahan had acquired Raja Jai Singh's palace.

393
00:17:37,231 --> 00:17:39,621
So he took one line from actual history,

394
00:17:39,621 --> 00:17:43,906
and the remaining part was fabricated by him with an active imagination.

395
00:17:43,906 --> 00:17:48,295
To be honest, P.N. Oak could have been a brilliant fiction author.

396
00:17:48,295 --> 00:17:53,425
But for some reason, he chose to be a self-proclaimed historian.

397
00:17:53,425 --> 00:17:56,089
Supreme Court had dismissed his petition saying that

398
00:17:56,089 --> 00:17:58,027
it was a misconceived notion,

399
00:17:58,027 --> 00:18:00,346
the Supreme Court had even ridiculed him,

400
00:18:00,346 --> 00:18:02,790
saying that it seemed he was bitten by a bee.

401
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:04,776
And so we arrive at 2010.

402
00:18:04,776 --> 00:18:06,252
WhatsApp started gaining traction.

403
00:18:06,252 --> 00:18:08,693
The WhatsApp University began.

404
00:18:08,693 --> 00:18:12,302
And the fictional tales of P.N. Oak,

405
00:18:12,302 --> 00:18:15,202
turn into theories of the WhatsApp University.

406
00:18:15,202 --> 00:18:18,881
When these fictional stories are forwarded time and again,

407
00:18:18,881 --> 00:18:19,884
and reach people.

408
00:18:19,884 --> 00:18:22,865
People start believing them to be true accounts,

409
00:18:22,865 --> 00:18:26,224
and then there are fresh petitions put to our courts.

410
00:18:26,224 --> 00:18:28,520
And then our courts have to waste their time on such futile petitions.

411
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:33,140
Interestingly, after being forwarded so many times in WhatsApp University,

412
00:18:33,140 --> 00:18:36,657
P.N. Oak had talked about the year 1155,

